<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
monophialidic to polyphialidic, arising from hyphae laterally, with an inflated base (7
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)7.5–10(–">-)7.5-10(-</normalizedToken>
11) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(2.5-) 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="–3.5(–">-3.5(-</normalizedToken>
4) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Conidia</emphasis>
hyaline, globose, 2.5-3 (-3.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, one-celled with warty surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="101">
